{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/autism-in-children/background-information/prevalence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"91c91a89-4d40-5a00-871a-7662ff9babb0","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 1aa8c403-464e-4732-a2f8-45e2e11da4dd --><h2>How common is it?</h2><!-- end field 1aa8c403-464e-4732-a2f8-45e2e11da4dd -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item b81fa5f0-6afd-4f9e-9d0c-cbcd8a468498 --><!-- begin field ac214dae-d6b5-40c0-9173-9878cf7de277 --><ul><li><strong>Autism spectrum disorder (ASD)</strong> <strong>is one of the most common childhood onset neurodevelopmental disorders </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/autism-in-children/references/\">BMJ, 2018a</a>]<strong>. </strong></li><li>The estimated prevalence in children is at least 1%, with relative consistency across studies [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/autism-in-children/references/\">SIGN, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/autism-in-children/references/\">National Collaborating Centre for Women&rsquo;s and Children&rsquo;s Health, 2017</a>].</li><li>There are about 3–4 times more boys affected by ASD than girls, although this varies across the spectrum. Girls are more likely to have a learning (intellectual) disability; however, there is anecdotal evidence that ASD may be under-recognized in girls without a learning (intellectual) disability [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/autism-in-children/references/\">American Psychiatric Association, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/autism-in-children/references/\">SIGN, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/autism-in-children/references/\">National Collaborating Centre for Women&rsquo;s and Children&rsquo;s Health, 2017</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field ac214dae-d6b5-40c0-9173-9878cf7de277 --><!-- end item b81fa5f0-6afd-4f9e-9d0c-cbcd8a468498 -->","topic":{"id":"3d9f48c8-37bc-5d75-8620-a889a3d26b6c","topicId":"dded286c-cea8-4cea-b71b-0d2fb3901796","topicName":"Autism in children","slug":"autism-in-children","lastRevised":"Last revised in August 2020","chapters":[{"id":"913c5826-d299-5de0-877e-e8aeb7b19fd6","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"691a24a8-98e4-5a92-b6f3-015075253332","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"3e6ac9c6-f1a6-58dd-8137-0754ab7ef812","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"b653efa1-762f-5230-8424-405a7d5b3231","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"1247dbf0-200e-55df-ac0e-cbc4c05c0060","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"579ed566-140b-55cf-b5d7-57ef8317c868","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"186b807b-09e0-5fd1-90f3-e9f60b6d6d69","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"1956c410-0e94-5cd1-9669-4f5221345eb5","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"7048a532-550b-5eb7-a26b-0e204d5eb736","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"7c396d39-31cd-5c19-a040-93603d4db12e","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"f6ad135c-4293-511d-bca4-54d43d5a712a","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"3d6d4d46-92b3-5790-9907-9d79fe8aa753","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE Quality standards"}]},{"id":"80fb020d-40db-59df-a6f6-4d6b4988b81e","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"2df6d4d0-ceb7-5e1c-bbd5-194e0bd3916a","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"c4